    <item>
      <title>Clinical Scribe</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/clinical-scribe/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/clinical-scribe/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You dictated some notes between patients. Now you need to turn them into a proper clinical document — with the right ICD-10 codes, CPT codes, and medication details. The Clinical Scribe agent does all of that for you.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;give-it-your-notes&#34;&gt;Give It Your Notes&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Paste your rough notes, a dictation transcript, or even bullet points. For example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;55yo male, HTN follow-up. BP 168/96, up from last visit. On lisinopril 20mg. Adding amlodipine 5mg. A1c 6.8 last month, discussing lifestyle changes. ECG normal sinus. Follow up 2 weeks.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Diagnostic Support</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/diagnostic-support/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/diagnostic-support/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A patient presents with a complex set of symptoms. You need the full picture — triage level, differential, codes, lab interpretation, medication review, and protocols. The Diagnostic Support agent runs all of that from a single prompt.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;give-it-the-clinical-picture&#34;&gt;Give It the Clinical Picture&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;62yo male, sudden crushing substernal chest pain radiating to left arm, diaphoresis, BP 92/58, HR 110. PMH: HTN, DM2, former smoker. Meds: metformin 1000mg BID, lisinopril 40mg, aspirin 81mg. Troponin pending.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Research Advisor</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/research-advisor/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/research-advisor/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You have a clinical question that requires a real evidence review — not just a quick answer, but what the studies show, what the FDA says, and whether any trials are running. The Research Advisor handles the whole thing.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;give-it-your-question&#34;&gt;Give It Your Question&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;What is the current evidence for SGLT2 inhibitors in heart failure with preserved ejection fraction?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-7-step-review&#34;&gt;The 7-Step Review&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-timeline&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Extract Research Terms&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Identifies the key concepts and builds optimized search queries.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.1); color: var(--primary);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128196;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Search Strategy&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Terms:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;SGLT2 inhibitors, HFpEF, dapagliflozin, empagliflozin, heart failure preserved ejection fraction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Filters:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;RCTs, systematic reviews, meta-analyses, 2020–2026&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Knowledge Base Search&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Searches Lumen&#39;s indexed clinical content for baseline context.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(14,165,233,0.1); color: var(--cyan);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128218;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Clinical Context&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;4 sources&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;ACC/AHA HF Guidelines &amp;middot; ESC HFpEF Position Paper &amp;middot; SGLT2i Class Review &amp;middot; HFpEF Diagnostic Criteria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;PubMed Literature&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;PubMed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Searches PubMed for peer-reviewed studies, fetches abstracts, ranks by relevance.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(14,165,233,0.1); color: var(--cyan);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128218;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;PubMed Results&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;12 articles&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34; style=&#34;flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Solomon SD et al. DELIVER (2022)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Dapagliflozin in HFpEF. NEJM. HR 0.82 (0.73–0.92) for worsening HF or CV death.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34; style=&#34;flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Anker SD et al. EMPEROR-Preserved (2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Empagliflozin in HFpEF. NEJM. HR 0.79 (0.69–0.90) for CV death or HF hospitalization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34; style=&#34;flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Vaduganathan M et al. (2022)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;SGLT2i across the HF spectrum: meta-analysis. Lancet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;FDA Drug Data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;OpenFDA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Checks FDA prescribing information, approved indications, and safety data.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(52,199,89,0.1); color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128138;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;FDA Label Data&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Dapagliflozin (Farxiga)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34; style=&#34;margin-left: auto; color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#10003; FDA-approved for HF (all EFs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Empagliflozin (Jardiance)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34; style=&#34;margin-left: auto; color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#10003; FDA-approved for HF (all EFs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Key warnings:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34; style=&#34;margin-left: auto;&#34;&gt;DKA risk, genital infections, volume depletion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;5&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Trials&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;ClinicalTrials.gov&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Searches for active and recently completed trials relevant to the question.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(140,102,217,0.1); color: var(--purple);&#34;&gt;&amp;#129514;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Active Trials&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;3 trials&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;NCT05396573&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;SGLT2i + GLP-1 RA combination in HFpEF (Phase 3, recruiting)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;NCT06012839&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Dapagliflozin in HFpEF with obesity (Phase 4, active)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;6&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Drug Normalization&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;RxNorm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Resolves drug names to canonical identifiers for accuracy.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(52,199,89,0.1); color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128138;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Drug Profile&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Class:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;SGLT2 inhibitor (sodium-glucose co-transporter 2)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Mechanism:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Blocks glucose reabsorption in proximal tubule → glycosuria, osmotic diuresis, cardioprotection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;&amp;#10003;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Evidence Synthesis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Combines all evidence into a structured review with conclusions and identified gaps.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(52,199,89,0.1); color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128203;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Literature Review&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;Final Report&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusion:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong evidence (2 large RCTs, meta-analyses) supports SGLT2i use in HFpEF. Both dapagliflozin and empagliflozin FDA-approved. NNT ~21 for HF hospitalization prevention. Active trials exploring combination therapy and subpopulations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tip-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-label&#34;&gt;&amp;#128161; Tip&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-title&#34;&gt;Attach a paper for context&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-body&#34;&gt;Upload a research paper in the Sources panel. The agent will use it as context — finding related studies, newer data, or contradicting evidence.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Insurance &amp; Appeals</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/insurance/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/insurance/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Prior auths and claim denials consume hours of your week. Lumen has two agents that do the heavy lifting — one for clinicians handling the paperwork, and one that aggressively fights denials on behalf of patients.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;insurance-manager&#34;&gt;Insurance Manager&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For clinicians and billing staff.&lt;/strong&gt; Describe the procedure and diagnosis, and the agent handles the rest.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Prior auth for MRI lumbar spine. 55yo with 6 weeks of radiculopathy, failed conservative management with PT and NSAIDs. Payer: UnitedHealthcare.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Document Analyzer</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/document-analyzer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/document-analyzer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You received a consult report, a research paper, or a lengthy clinical document. You need the key findings organized, mapped to codes, and backed with evidence. Upload the document and let the agent do the rest.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;upload-and-ask&#34;&gt;Upload and Ask&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Attach a PDF or paste the text in the Sources panel, then type:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Analyze this cardiology consult and summarize the key findings and recommendations&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-7-step-analysis&#34;&gt;The 7-Step Analysis&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-timeline&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Summarize Document&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Creates a comprehensive executive summary of the entire document.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.1); color: var(--primary);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128196;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Executive Summary&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;68yo male referred for evaluation of new systolic murmur. Echo reveals moderate-severe aortic stenosis (AVA 0.9 cm², mean gradient 38 mmHg). LVEF preserved at 58%. Coronary angiography recommended prior to valve intervention...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Extract Entities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Identifies all clinical entities — conditions, medications, procedures, lab values, measurements.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(140,102,217,0.1); color: var(--purple);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128196;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Clinical Entities&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Conditions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;aortic stenosis (moderate-severe), exertional dyspnea&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Measurements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;AVA 0.9 cm², mean gradient 38 mmHg, LVEF 58%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Medications:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;lisinopril, atorvastatin, aspirin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Procedures:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;echocardiogram, coronary angiography (recommended)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Extract Keywords&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Pulls the primary clinical topics for literature searching.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.1); color: var(--primary);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128196;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Key Topics&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;aortic stenosis, TAVR, surgical AVR, valve area, gradient, exercise tolerance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Knowledge Base Search&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Searches for relevant clinical guidelines and context.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(14,165,233,0.1); color: var(--cyan);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128218;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Guidelines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;3 sources&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;ACC/AHA Valvular Heart Disease Guidelines 2023 &amp;middot; AS Intervention Criteria &amp;middot; TAVR vs SAVR Decision Framework&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;5&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;PubMed Literature&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;PubMed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Finds supporting or contradicting evidence from peer-reviewed studies.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(14,165,233,0.1); color: var(--cyan);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128218;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;PubMed Results&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;8 articles&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34; style=&#34;flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;PARTNER 3 (2019)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;TAVR vs SAVR in low-risk patients. NEJM.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34; style=&#34;flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Carabello BA (2023)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Timing of intervention in AS. Circulation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;6&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Diagnostic Codes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;ICD-10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(255,149,0,0.1); color: var(--orange);&#34;&gt;&amp;#127973;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;ICD-10 Codes&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;I35.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Nonrheumatic aortic (valve) stenosis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;R06.00&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Dyspnea, unspecified&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;&amp;#10003;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Structured Analysis Report&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Combines everything into an organized report: summary, key findings, ICD-10 codes, supporting evidence, and clinical recommendations.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(52,199,89,0.1); color: var(--green);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128203;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Analysis Report&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;Final Report&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Summary &amp;middot; 6 key findings &amp;middot; 2 ICD-10 codes &amp;middot; 8 supporting articles &amp;middot; 3 guideline citations &amp;middot; Recommended next steps: coronary angio, valve clinic referral, STS risk score&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;tip-card&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-label&#34;&gt;&amp;#128161; Tip&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-title&#34;&gt;Compare multiple documents&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;tip-body&#34;&gt;Upload several documents — reports over time, or competing guidelines — and ask the agent to compare them.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Health Explainer</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/health-explainer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/health-explainer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Your patient just got a diagnosis, a lab result, or a medication change. They look confused. The Health Explainer takes complex medical content and translates it into clear, plain language at an 8th grade reading level — something they can actually read at home.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;paste-the-medical-content&#34;&gt;Paste the Medical Content&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Newly diagnosed atrial fibrillation with RVR, CHA2DS2-VASc 4, started on apixaban 5mg BID and metoprolol succinate 50mg daily. Echo: mild LA dilation, EF 55%. Cardioversion not planned.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Symptom Checker</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/agents/symptom-checker/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/agents/symptom-checker/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Describe a patient&amp;rsquo;s symptoms. The Symptom Checker runs a systematic 8-step evaluation — ESI triage, guideline review, coding, lab interpretation, and protocol recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;describe-the-presentation&#34;&gt;Describe the Presentation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;45yo female, sudden onset worst headache of her life, 10/10 severity, nausea, neck stiffness. BP 180/100, HR 88. No prior headache history, no trauma.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-each-step-produces&#34;&gt;What Each Step Produces&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-timeline&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;1&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Extract Symptoms &amp; History&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Parses the presentation into structured clinical findings.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(88,101,242,0.1); color: var(--primary);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128196;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Structured Findings&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Chief Complaint:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Thunderclap headache, 10/10, sudden onset&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Associated:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Nausea, nuchal rigidity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34;&gt;Vitals:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;BP 180/100 (hypertensive), HR 88&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-label&#34; style=&#34;color: var(--red);&#34;&gt;Red flags:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34; style=&#34;color: var(--red);&#34;&gt;&#34;Worst headache of life&#34; + neck stiffness + HTN → SAH until proven otherwise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;2&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;ESI Triage Assessment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;Triage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(229,62,62,0.1); color: var(--red);&#34;&gt;&amp;#127973;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Triage Result&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-type&#34;&gt;ESI Level&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;&#34;&gt;&#xA;          &lt;span style=&#34;font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--red);&#34;&gt;ESI 1&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;          &lt;span class=&#34;mini-severity major&#34;&gt;Immediate life threat&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Thunderclap headache with meningismus — SAH must be emergently ruled out. Immediate CT head without contrast.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;3&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Clinical Guidelines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Searches for applicable clinical guidelines.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(14,165,233,0.1); color: var(--cyan);&#34;&gt;&amp;#128218;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Guidelines&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;AHA/ASA SAH Guidelines &amp;middot; Ottawa SAH Rule &amp;middot; ACR Appropriateness Criteria: Headache&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;4&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Triage Criteria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;Triage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-desc&#34;&gt;Loads ESI severity definitions and decision rules.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;5&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Diagnostic Codes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;ICD-10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(255,149,0,0.1); color: var(--orange);&#34;&gt;&amp;#127973;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;ICD-10 Codes&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-content&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;I60.9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Nontraumatic SAH, unspecified (working dx)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;R51.9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Headache, unspecified (if SAH ruled out)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mini-row&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-code&#34;&gt;R29.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mini-value&#34;&gt;Meningismus&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;step-item&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-dot&#34;&gt;6&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-body&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-item-header&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-name&#34;&gt;Lab Reference Ranges&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;step-item-tool&#34;&gt;Lab Ranges&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-bar&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;step-artifact-icon&#34; style=&#34;background: rgba(61,191,128,0.1); color: var(--teal);&#34;&gt;&amp;#129514;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;step-artifact-label&#34;&gt;Expected Labs&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &lt;div class=&#34;ste